'''Brian ''"Rookie"'' Wilson''' (born [[September 14]], [[1967]]) is an [[United States|American]] [[real estate]] developer and [[poker]] player, originally from [[Rockford, Illinois|Rockford]], [[Illinois]], now based in [[Fort Myers, Florida|Fort Myers]], [[Florida]].

Wilson won a [[World Series of Poker]] [[WSOP bracelet|bracelet]] in [[2005 World Series of Poker|2005]] in the $5,000 [[betting (poker)|pot limit]] [[hold'em]] event, defeating [[John Gale (poker player)|John Gale]] in the final heads-up confrontation to take home the $370,685 first prize. This was the first pot limit event Wilson had ever played. He has noted that this was event #20 at the WSOP, started on June 20th, and 20 is his lucky number.

Wilson also appeared in the televised [[William Hill Poker Grand Prix]] (heat 6). The "rookie" took 2nd place in the 888.com UK Open and participated in the very 1st Poker Dome show in Las Vegas. In 2007 Wilson Finished 13th in the $5k main event of the Tunica WSOP circuit event.

Wilson claims to be a disciple of [[Dave Colclough|Dave "El Blondie" Colclough]], who tutored him in poker after they met in [[Estonia]] during [[September 2004]]. Wilson has since [[Hair coloring|dyed]] his hair blonde and become involved with the BlondePoker website. Recent posts on BlondePoker, however, discount this saying that he is a dormant memeber of the BlondePoker world.

As of 2007, his total live tournament winnings exceed $800,000. Wilson has done commentary for Bluff radio and the World Series of Poker and is planning to chase the 2008 European Player of the year award. Known for his carefree attitude Wilson enjoys playing at all levels and is never afraid of a good prop bet. Since the 2007 WSOP Wilson has been playing poker at the "One eyed Jacks" poker room in Sarasota , Florida.